2
00:00:10,160 --> 00:00:11,720
I want to know.

3
00:00:12,020 --> 00:00:14,790
What happened between you and the old peach?

4
00:00:15,040 --> 00:00:17,770
He just didn’t want to live like that anymore.

5
00:00:18,320 --> 00:00:20,220
Once I’ve made a decision,

6
00:00:21,220 --> 00:00:22,370
I never change my mind.

7
00:00:23,830 --> 00:00:25,960
We won’t regret it.

8
00:00:26,460 --> 00:00:28,290
We won’t regret it.

9
00:00:29,790 --> 00:00:31,100
Don’t let go of my hand.

10
00:00:32,950 --> 00:00:34,200
I promise.

11
00:01:42,479 --> 00:01:43,380
You.

12
00:01:48,200 --> 00:01:51,710
Hey, you… wake up. You’ll be late for work.

13
00:01:55,470 --> 00:01:56,979
I know.

14
00:01:58,030 --> 00:02:00,370
Can I enjoy this a little longer?

15
00:02:00,820 --> 00:02:02,180
Hey, you.

16
00:02:02,180 --> 00:02:05,590
If you’re late for work, that’s not on me.

17
00:02:11,360 --> 00:02:13,100
Give me a morning kiss.

18
00:02:13,700 --> 00:02:15,150
So I’ll have the energy for work.

19
00:02:26,329 --> 00:02:27,950
The energy’s not here yet.

20
00:02:34,320 --> 00:02:35,500
Better keep sleeping.

21
00:02:36,290 --> 00:02:37,329
Honestly, you…

22
00:02:45,360 --> 00:02:46,510
Just like this,

23
00:02:46,510 --> 00:02:48,160
now I finally have the energy for work.

24
00:02:48,810 --> 00:02:50,790
However long you want to shoot, I’m ready.

25
00:02:53,950 --> 00:02:55,010
Go take a shower.

26
00:03:44,120 --> 00:03:46,280
Maybe I should go help Sasom shower.

27
00:03:54,120 --> 00:03:55,050
You.

28
00:03:55,450 --> 00:03:57,040
I’ll scrub your back.

29
00:04:24,120 --> 00:04:27,190
How do you feel about your brother getting married?

30
00:04:30,760 --> 00:04:31,850
Well…

31
00:04:31,850 --> 00:04:33,080
I’m happy for him.

32
00:04:34,680 --> 00:04:36,520
Seeing him happy

33
00:04:37,870 --> 00:04:39,280
makes me happy too.

34
00:04:41,690 --> 00:04:43,320
And it kind of feels like…

35
00:04:43,870 --> 00:04:45,780
I’m gaining another family member.

36
00:04:52,480 --> 00:04:54,409
I don’t know.

37
00:04:56,020 --> 00:04:57,180
I never really thought about it before.

38
00:04:58,640 --> 00:04:59,770
All this time,

39
00:05:00,620 --> 00:05:01,900
my family

40
00:05:03,460 --> 00:05:06,600
has always cared about reputation and business.

41
00:05:08,910 --> 00:05:11,860
Only my brother is the exception.

42
00:05:12,820 --> 00:05:14,360
For him, love and business

43
00:05:15,370 --> 00:05:16,650
can go together just fine.

44
00:05:18,260 --> 00:05:19,500
Because of that,

45
00:05:20,350 --> 00:05:21,620
I never paid much attention to it.

46
00:05:28,040 --> 00:05:28,890
But…

47
00:05:30,600 --> 00:05:31,400
who knows.

48
00:05:35,440 --> 00:05:36,570
Because now,

49
00:05:37,330 --> 00:05:39,520
I’m starting to care.

50
00:05:42,640 --> 00:05:43,430
What about you?

51
00:05:52,120 --> 00:05:53,560
I think…

52
00:05:54,760 --> 00:05:57,540
marriage can’t guarantee love at all.

53
00:05:58,650 --> 00:05:59,870
Just look at…

54
00:06:00,000 --> 00:06:01,200
my parents.

55
00:06:03,870 --> 00:06:05,790
I can’t even imagine

56
00:06:05,790 --> 00:06:07,610
how people who get married

57
00:06:08,870 --> 00:06:10,920
decide that

58
00:06:11,620 --> 00:06:12,780
this is the person they’ll marry.

59
00:06:20,360 --> 00:06:21,700
But now,

60
00:06:24,480 --> 00:06:25,610
I think…

61
00:06:34,120 --> 00:06:36,010
I can picture it now.

62
00:06:57,880 --> 00:06:58,900
What does it look like?

63
00:07:02,800 --> 00:07:03,730
Is it dry yet?

64
00:07:04,330 --> 00:07:05,430
Not yet.

65
00:07:05,680 --> 00:07:07,530
It’s dry now… right?

66
00:07:44,000 --> 00:07:45,100
Hello, Khun Ngern.

67
00:07:45,760 --> 00:07:46,940
What can I do for you?

68
00:07:49,440 --> 00:07:52,390
The day after tomorrow, pick up a guest at the airport for me.

69
00:07:53,490 --> 00:07:54,270
A guest…

70
00:07:54,620 --> 00:07:55,320
a special one.

71
00:07:56,720 --> 00:07:57,220
Alright.

72
00:07:58,470 --> 00:08:01,600
I’ll send you the details after the call.

73
00:08:01,800 --> 00:08:02,300
Oh…

74
00:08:02,610 --> 00:08:04,500
And don’t let my younger brother know.

75
00:08:04,760 --> 00:08:05,620
I don’t want this to become a problem.

76
00:08:07,680 --> 00:08:08,500
Do you understand, Inn?

77
00:08:09,450 --> 00:08:10,520
I understand.

78
00:08:11,480 --> 00:08:12,210
Good.

79
00:08:12,510 --> 00:08:13,910
I’ll transfer the money later.

80
00:08:15,920 --> 00:08:16,750
Thank you.

81
00:09:41,560 --> 00:09:42,480
Did you know

82
00:09:42,730 --> 00:09:47,180
a peach isn’t just a fruit?

83
00:09:48,330 --> 00:09:49,100
It can also mean

84
00:09:49,500 --> 00:09:51,470
facing reality.

85
00:09:53,220 --> 00:09:55,220
The peach’s soft, alluring skin

86
00:09:55,520 --> 00:09:56,660
is like the image

87
00:09:57,310 --> 00:09:59,200
we wish the world to see as beautiful

88
00:10:00,150 --> 00:10:00,780
smooth

89
00:10:01,480 --> 00:10:02,540
and flawless.

90
00:10:04,550 --> 00:10:05,930
But when you truly bite into it,

91
00:10:06,780 --> 00:10:08,080
you discover a flavor

92
00:10:08,680 --> 00:10:09,460
that’s both sweet

93
00:10:10,310 --> 00:10:11,550
and sour at the same time.

94
00:10:13,450 --> 00:10:14,980
Relationships are the same.

95
00:10:15,840 --> 00:10:17,840
Nothing is ever completely perfect.

96
00:10:18,540 --> 00:10:19,770
Happiness and sweetness

97
00:10:20,580 --> 00:10:22,640
often come with the sourness of problems

98
00:10:23,540 --> 00:10:25,350
and truths that are hard to accept.

99
00:10:25,950 --> 00:10:26,910
And sometimes,

100
00:10:27,510 --> 00:10:28,780
loving someone

101
00:10:30,000 --> 00:10:32,940
isn’t just about savoring the sweetness that fills your heart.

102
00:10:33,740 --> 00:10:36,470
It’s about accepting every flavor that comes with them.

103
00:10:37,320 --> 00:10:38,850
Like taking a bite of a peach

104
00:10:39,750 --> 00:10:40,840
that brings both joy

105
00:10:41,440 --> 00:10:42,320
and pain

106
00:10:42,870 --> 00:10:44,550
and helps us grow at the same time.

107
00:11:14,120 --> 00:11:15,660
Once I’ve made a decision,

108
00:11:18,400 --> 00:11:19,750
I never change my mind.

109
00:11:33,760 --> 00:11:35,360
We won’t regret it.

110
00:11:37,420 --> 00:11:38,940
We won’t regret it.

111
00:12:21,400 --> 00:12:21,900
Hello.

112
00:12:24,660 --> 00:12:25,870
It’s been a long time.

113
00:12:27,170 --> 00:12:28,270
Why?

114
00:12:28,670 --> 00:12:29,840
Did you miss me?

115
00:12:30,600 --> 00:12:31,940
Of course I did.

116
00:12:34,850 --> 00:12:36,000
So straightforward.

117
00:12:37,200 --> 00:12:38,930
Are you coming to see me tonight?

118
00:12:41,430 --> 00:12:42,430
If you do,

119
00:12:44,240 --> 00:12:45,820
I’ll cook and wait for you.

120
00:12:48,680 --> 00:12:49,700
That’s the problem.

121
00:12:52,300 --> 00:12:53,350
Honestly,

122
00:12:54,200 --> 00:12:55,380
I can’t come over.

123
00:12:56,530 --> 00:12:58,560
Because I don’t want to eat your cooking.

124
00:12:58,860 --> 00:13:00,000
Why not?

125
00:13:00,800 --> 00:13:01,500
Because it’s too good.

126
00:13:02,610 --> 00:13:03,560
If I go,

127
00:13:04,310 --> 00:13:05,350
I won’t be able to resist.

128
00:13:06,100 --> 00:13:07,830
And then my diet

129
00:13:08,630 --> 00:13:09,800
will be ruined.

130
00:13:12,170 --> 00:13:13,610
The director told me to lose weight.

131
00:13:14,010 --> 00:13:14,780
He said…

132
00:13:15,230 --> 00:13:16,520
I’m starting to get too chubby.

133
00:13:16,720 --> 00:13:21,240
The lead at the beginning of the story and the lead at the end—

134
00:13:26,000 --> 00:13:27,660
But I really want to eat your cooking.

135
00:13:30,600 --> 00:13:31,170
Yeah.

136
00:13:32,380 --> 00:13:33,200
And…

137
00:13:34,060 --> 00:13:35,160
I miss you a lot too.

138
00:13:40,000 --> 00:13:41,520
I miss you too.

139
00:13:42,870 --> 00:13:44,160
Kiss kiss.

140
00:14:25,440 --> 00:14:26,480
Excuse me?

141
00:14:26,730 --> 00:14:28,110
Is anyone here?

142
00:14:37,960 --> 00:14:38,820
Sorry about that.

143
00:14:39,770 --> 00:14:40,270
Come in.

144
00:14:40,270 --> 00:14:42,180
Young master, it’s me.

145
00:14:42,530 --> 00:14:43,590
Aunt Por.

146
00:14:44,040 --> 00:14:45,430
Do you remember me?

147
00:14:45,780 --> 00:14:46,780
Aunt Por.

148
00:14:47,540 --> 00:14:48,910
Please come inside quickly.

149
00:14:49,160 --> 00:14:50,370
It’s hot outside.

150
00:14:50,870 --> 00:14:52,010
Thank you, young master.

151
00:14:52,260 --> 00:14:52,890
Yes.

152
00:14:53,190 --> 00:14:54,520
Come, have a seat first, Auntie.

153
00:14:59,680 --> 00:15:00,850
Oh, Auntie—

154
00:15:01,500 --> 00:15:02,700
Please sit on the sofa.

155
00:15:04,260 --> 00:15:05,420
Come sit here.

156
00:15:11,480 --> 00:15:12,600
Thank you, young master.

157
00:15:13,200 --> 00:15:14,610
You’re being too polite, Auntie.

158
00:15:15,310 --> 00:15:16,880
There’s no need to be so polite, Auntie.

159
00:15:17,430 --> 00:15:18,880
Please make yourself comfortable.

160
00:15:20,000 --> 00:15:20,500
Alright.

161
00:15:28,120 --> 00:15:29,720
It’s been a long time.

162
00:15:30,420 --> 00:15:31,620
I never thought…

163
00:15:31,920 --> 00:15:33,070
we’d meet again today.

164
00:15:36,180 --> 00:15:37,410
That’s true.

165
00:15:38,160 --> 00:15:39,770
The last time we met,

166
00:15:41,520 --> 00:15:43,380
you still looked so young.

167
00:15:44,780 --> 00:15:46,170
Look at you now—

168
00:15:47,030 --> 00:15:48,470
tall and well-built.

169
00:15:53,900 --> 00:15:57,500
Actually, I didn’t mean to bother you.

170
00:15:59,450 --> 00:16:02,040
But since I won’t be here anymore…

171
00:16:03,850 --> 00:16:07,620
I wanted to come say goodbye to you once.

172
00:16:11,330 --> 00:16:12,190
Say goodbye?

173
00:16:14,100 --> 00:16:15,340
Where are you going?

174
00:16:18,550 --> 00:16:20,000
I’m going back to Lopburi.

175
00:16:23,240 --> 00:16:25,040
My son…

176
00:16:25,750 --> 00:16:27,370
he remarried.

177
00:16:28,020 --> 00:16:30,440
So he wants me to move in with him.

178
00:16:31,640 --> 00:16:33,400
That way he can take care of me.

179
00:16:35,710 --> 00:16:37,110
Then…

180
00:16:38,170 --> 00:16:39,180
does that mean

181
00:16:40,000 --> 00:16:42,140
you resigned from my father’s house?

182
00:16:46,000 --> 00:16:47,300
Yes, I resigned.

183
00:16:59,760 --> 00:17:01,380
Are you alright, Auntie?

184
00:17:04,010 --> 00:17:04,859
I’m fine.

185
00:17:05,560 --> 00:17:11,050
I just know you don’t like hearing about your father.

186
00:17:11,700 --> 00:17:13,700
So I didn’t dare say much.

187
00:17:14,700 --> 00:17:15,710
It’s alright.

188
00:17:16,609 --> 00:17:17,660
I’m okay now.

189
00:17:19,210 --> 00:17:20,160
Besides,

190
00:17:20,359 --> 00:17:21,420
my father and I

191
00:17:22,020 --> 00:17:23,099
have nothing to do with each other anymore.

192
00:17:28,260 --> 00:17:29,060
By the way,

193
00:17:30,510 --> 00:17:31,920
how is my father doing?

194
00:17:32,820 --> 00:17:34,020
How is his treatment going?

195
00:17:38,560 --> 00:17:39,560
Not well.

196
00:17:40,610 --> 00:17:42,740
His condition hasn’t improved.

197
00:17:43,350 --> 00:17:44,170
Probably because

198
00:17:44,920 --> 00:17:47,170
he isn’t serious about treatment.

199
00:17:48,120 --> 00:17:49,940
So it only keeps getting worse.

200
00:17:51,340 --> 00:17:52,090
That’s strange.

201
00:17:52,790 --> 00:17:54,450
My father has so much money.

202
00:17:55,000 --> 00:17:56,750
He could find the best doctors.

203
00:17:56,950 --> 00:18:00,400
Money isn’t the problem, young master.

204
00:18:01,650 --> 00:18:07,000
The problem is he spends it in the wrong place.

205
00:18:09,610 --> 00:18:10,810
The wrong place?

206
00:18:14,420 --> 00:18:15,050
Yes.

207
00:18:15,800 --> 00:18:16,870
The wrong place.

208
00:18:18,930 --> 00:18:20,550
Instead of seeing real doctors,

209
00:18:21,800 --> 00:18:23,430
he goes to fortune tellers.

210
00:18:25,040 --> 00:18:26,590
Then how

211
00:18:26,590 --> 00:18:28,330
could he possibly get better?

212
00:18:38,500 --> 00:18:39,410
Young master,

213
00:18:40,560 --> 00:18:42,790
have you heard about Master Long?

214
00:18:46,650 --> 00:18:48,170
The one who got arrested?

215
00:18:50,730 --> 00:18:51,990
No.

216
00:18:53,290 --> 00:19:00,150
About how your father gave money to powerful people.

217
00:19:01,710 --> 00:19:02,810
What?

218
00:19:05,870 --> 00:19:07,390
It’s true.

219
00:19:08,740 --> 00:19:12,550
I heard millions were paid.

220
00:19:15,400 --> 00:19:18,020
And after that it caused a huge scandal.

221
00:19:20,230 --> 00:19:21,760
So, Khun Praew

222
00:19:23,360 --> 00:19:25,870
had to take Khun Phong and run away.

223
00:19:28,730 --> 00:19:30,170
Does that mean…

224
00:19:30,720 --> 00:19:31,950
Khun Praew and my father

225
00:19:33,650 --> 00:19:34,980
are divorced now?

226
00:19:36,230 --> 00:19:37,970
How could they not divorce?

227
00:19:39,620 --> 00:19:43,700
It’s good she didn’t put up with it this time.

228
00:19:44,550 --> 00:19:47,580
She took her child back to her father’s house the next day.

229
00:19:49,230 --> 00:19:50,710
Did my father accept that?

230
00:19:51,660 --> 00:19:53,320
He had no choice.

231
00:20:02,590 --> 00:20:03,490
Right now,

232
00:20:07,400 --> 00:20:09,080
the one I worry about most

233
00:20:10,000 --> 00:20:11,500
is you, young master.

234
00:20:14,860 --> 00:20:15,560
Young master…

235
00:20:18,160 --> 00:20:20,100
please be careful.

236
00:20:23,910 --> 00:20:24,930
Why?

237
00:20:30,200 --> 00:20:32,810
I heard the bodyguards talking.

238
00:20:33,860 --> 00:20:36,560
They said your father hates you deeply.

239
00:20:40,800 --> 00:20:42,390
You understand, right?

240
00:20:49,520 --> 00:20:50,540
I understand.

241
00:21:16,600 --> 00:21:17,660
Hello, son.

242
00:21:20,470 --> 00:21:22,400
I just stopped by to say goodbye to my employer.

243
00:21:25,210 --> 00:21:26,500
I’ll head back soon.

244
00:22:02,280 --> 00:22:03,650
I can’t accept this.

245
00:22:04,000 --> 00:22:04,930
Please take it.

246
00:22:05,480 --> 00:22:06,380
Don’t worry about it.

247
00:22:07,840 --> 00:22:08,660
But…

248
00:22:09,560 --> 00:22:10,440
Think of it

249
00:22:11,990 --> 00:22:12,980
as my way of thanking you

250
00:22:15,490 --> 00:22:17,700
for taking care of my mother and me.

251
00:22:25,200 --> 00:22:26,820
Thank you so much, young master.

252
00:22:30,400 --> 00:22:31,850
I wish you

253
00:22:32,850 --> 00:22:34,170
a very happy life.

254
00:22:37,720 --> 00:22:39,650
May you encounter only good things.

255
00:22:42,200 --> 00:22:44,210
May all your suffering finally end.

256
00:22:58,960 --> 00:23:00,720
Take good care of yourself.

257
00:23:02,270 --> 00:23:03,380
You too, Auntie.

258
00:23:25,720 --> 00:23:33,150
It’s the wedding day.

259
00:24:10,940 --> 00:24:12,100
There are so many people.

260
00:24:15,320 --> 00:24:16,740
But…

261
00:24:17,390 --> 00:24:19,000
why aren’t you inside?

262
00:24:20,000 --> 00:24:21,360
It’s your brother’s wedding.

263
00:24:22,310 --> 00:24:23,100
Oh, come on.

264
00:24:23,800 --> 00:24:25,350
I’ve been taking care of P’Ngern since morning.

265
00:24:26,250 --> 00:24:27,650
I just slipped out to see you for a bit.

266
00:24:28,200 --> 00:24:29,380
He won’t mind.

267
00:24:31,980 --> 00:24:33,250
Come on, let’s go inside.

268
00:24:49,360 --> 00:24:50,000
Hey—

269
00:24:51,450 --> 00:24:51,970
Po.

270
00:24:54,680 --> 00:24:56,090
Hello, P’Ngern. Hello, P’Pin.

271
00:24:56,390 --> 00:24:57,550
No need for that.

272
00:24:57,550 --> 00:24:59,160
Sasom said we’re about the same age.

273
00:24:59,410 --> 00:25:00,650
A handshake will do.

274
00:25:00,650 --> 00:25:01,400
Alright.

275
00:25:04,400 --> 00:25:06,430
Oh, Lek. That’s all?

276
00:25:09,040 --> 00:25:10,650
Then I’ll go check on the guests over there.

277
00:25:10,650 --> 00:25:11,510
Make yourselves comfortable.

278
00:25:11,510 --> 00:25:12,010
Sure.

279
00:25:12,210 --> 00:25:13,050
Thank you.

280
00:25:17,920 --> 00:25:19,070
I want to get married too.

281
00:25:20,320 --> 00:25:21,420
Oh, Po.

282
00:25:21,770 --> 00:25:22,990
You’re here.

283
00:25:23,340 --> 00:25:24,040
Cheers.

284
00:25:24,040 --> 00:25:25,190
Vic.

285
00:25:25,440 --> 00:25:26,780
If you’re drunk, don’t sit over there.

286
00:25:26,780 --> 00:25:27,480
Come here.

287
00:25:27,480 --> 00:25:28,610
I’m not drunk.

288
00:25:30,510 --> 00:25:31,570
You’ve got a weak tolerance.

289
00:25:36,600 --> 00:25:37,670
Is something wrong?

290
00:25:39,520 --> 00:25:41,550
I want to know

291
00:25:41,860 --> 00:25:43,810
how things are going with the clip.

292
00:25:45,210 --> 00:25:45,970
Well…

293
00:25:47,720 --> 00:25:48,970
we haven’t started anything yet.

294
00:25:52,000 --> 00:25:53,180
Why…

295
00:25:53,430 --> 00:25:55,070
do you say nothing has started yet?

296
00:25:55,420 --> 00:25:56,480
It’s been quite a while already.

297
00:25:58,680 --> 00:26:00,290
You should ask Sasom.

298
00:26:01,190 --> 00:26:02,780
I don’t know if he forgot about the clip or not.

299
00:26:06,130 --> 00:26:07,260
What are you talking about?

300
00:26:09,560 --> 00:26:11,850
You two moved in together because of the clip.

301
00:26:15,200 --> 00:26:18,160
But now you live together and don’t even film it.

302
00:26:18,910 --> 00:26:20,290
So what’s the point of living together?

303
00:26:20,640 --> 00:26:21,780
Thana.

304
00:26:23,440 --> 00:26:24,080
Hey.

305
00:26:30,120 --> 00:26:31,510
Don’t listen to him, Po.

306
00:26:35,560 --> 00:26:36,950
I’m going to the restroom for a bit.

307
00:26:42,160 --> 00:26:43,190
Po.

308
00:27:30,040 --> 00:27:31,080
I’m sorry.

309
00:27:34,720 --> 00:27:35,300
But…

310
00:27:36,290 --> 00:27:37,280
Don’t stay here alone.

311
00:27:42,480 --> 00:27:43,380
I’m sorry.

312
00:27:46,160 --> 00:27:47,870
I should be the one apologizing.

313
00:27:50,430 --> 00:27:52,770
I have answers to everything you want to know.

314
00:28:00,920 --> 00:28:03,100
I won’t let you misunderstand me again.

315
00:28:09,640 --> 00:28:11,020
Then tell me.

316
00:28:17,320 --> 00:28:18,560
Well…

317
00:28:18,560 --> 00:28:19,190
I…

318
00:28:19,190 --> 00:28:20,370
Sorry, man.

319
00:28:22,160 --> 00:28:24,820
Pin told me to come get you. P’Ngern is looking for you.

320
00:28:25,390 --> 00:28:27,110
Alright, give me five minutes.

321
00:28:27,640 --> 00:28:29,630
Actually… you have to go now.

322
00:28:30,530 --> 00:28:31,840
The dancing is about to start.

323
00:28:32,640 --> 00:28:34,150
But P’Ngern isn’t cooperating at all.

324
00:28:34,750 --> 00:28:35,990
He’s really drunk.

325
00:28:36,490 --> 00:28:37,600
He keeps yelling for you.

326
00:28:39,510 --> 00:28:40,350
Damn it.

327
00:28:42,650 --> 00:28:43,600
Hey.

328
00:28:43,950 --> 00:28:44,600
I think

329
00:28:45,960 --> 00:28:47,320
we should go back inside.

330
00:28:50,080 --> 00:28:51,990
It’s time.

331
00:28:51,990 --> 00:28:55,240
Please give a round of applause for the bride and groom.

332
00:29:06,160 --> 00:29:08,270
Alright everyone, please listen up.

333
00:29:08,470 --> 00:29:12,500
Today we have an activity for everyone to enjoy.

334
00:29:12,700 --> 00:29:16,290
Now I’ll hand the mic to our main sponsor today.

335
00:29:17,750 --> 00:29:18,250
Yes.

336
00:29:18,250 --> 00:29:18,910
Thank you.

337
00:29:19,110 --> 00:29:20,590
First of all,

338
00:29:20,590 --> 00:29:24,490
Pin would like to thank everyone for staying with us until now.

339
00:29:24,890 --> 00:29:25,590
Today,

340
00:29:25,790 --> 00:29:28,370
Ngern and I will be giving cash prizes

341
00:29:28,370 --> 00:29:33,190
to the three couples whose dancing we like the most.

342
00:29:35,640 --> 00:29:36,940
Dance your hearts out.

343
00:29:37,540 --> 00:29:39,760
Before we start the activity,

344
00:29:39,760 --> 00:29:43,080
let’s have the bride toss the bouquet first.

345
00:29:43,080 --> 00:29:44,400
Everyone, please come to the front of the stage.

346
00:29:44,400 --> 00:29:45,210
All couples.

347
00:29:45,210 --> 00:29:46,140
Everyone come forward.

348
00:29:47,400 --> 00:29:47,900
Alright.

349
00:29:47,900 --> 00:29:48,520
Please turn around.

350
00:29:48,520 --> 00:29:49,790
Is everyone ready?

351
00:29:49,790 --> 00:29:51,210
One, two, three!

352
00:29:56,680 --> 00:29:59,310
Oh, congratulations!

353
00:30:41,720 --> 00:30:42,820
Your name is Po, right?

354
00:30:43,870 --> 00:30:44,800
Have you thought this through?

355
00:30:45,800 --> 00:30:47,820
To become my new peach.

356
00:30:48,980 --> 00:30:49,800
Yes, I have.

357
00:30:53,840 --> 00:30:54,600
Sasom.

358
00:30:56,860 --> 00:30:59,290
Honestly, that day I was really surprised.

359
00:31:00,450 --> 00:31:01,710
When I found out you were still a virgin.

360
00:31:03,460 --> 00:31:05,320
You’re my new peach now.

361
00:31:19,200 --> 00:31:20,400
How did you get here?

362
00:31:27,520 --> 00:31:29,100
Once I’ve made a decision,

363
00:31:31,310 --> 00:31:32,480
I never change my mind.

364
00:31:33,890 --> 00:31:35,280
We won’t regret it.

365
00:31:37,280 --> 00:31:38,570
We won’t regret it.

366
00:32:08,960 --> 00:32:09,800
Hello, Lek.

367
00:32:11,610 --> 00:32:12,120
Ton.

368
00:32:33,680 --> 00:32:35,060
Long time no see.

369
00:32:39,280 --> 00:32:40,210
It’s me, Ton.

370
00:32:41,110 --> 00:32:42,110
Why?

371
00:32:42,910 --> 00:32:44,610
Why do you look like you’ve seen a ghost?

372
00:32:54,440 --> 00:32:56,170
The old peach is back.

373
00:33:02,520 --> 00:33:03,810
Well…

374
00:33:04,560 --> 00:33:05,830
I’m sorry.

375
00:33:07,930 --> 00:33:09,180
Sorry for what?

376
00:33:11,120 --> 00:33:11,620
I…

377
00:33:11,620 --> 00:33:12,780
I’m sorry for everything.

378
00:33:13,430 --> 00:33:14,820
For what I did.

379
00:33:15,470 --> 00:33:19,570
I didn’t mean it in a bad way.

380
00:33:20,220 --> 00:33:22,930
I just wanted everything to work out.

381
00:33:23,130 --> 00:33:26,800
I wanted everyone to understand what we were doing.

382
00:33:27,760 --> 00:33:29,840
I wanted the two of you

383
00:33:31,200 --> 00:33:32,460
to grow closer.

384
00:33:33,010 --> 00:33:34,990
To be more intimate.

385
00:33:35,340 --> 00:33:36,610
And I didn’t understand

386
00:33:36,810 --> 00:33:37,960
why Sasom…

387
00:33:37,960 --> 00:33:39,550
reacted the way he did.

388
00:33:40,750 --> 00:33:42,020
So it made me

389
00:33:43,070 --> 00:33:45,120
do something like this.

390
00:33:45,520 --> 00:33:46,770
I’m truly sorry.

391
00:33:48,670 --> 00:33:49,590
I’m sorry.

392
00:33:50,490 --> 00:33:51,280
It’s okay.

393
00:33:51,780 --> 00:33:52,800
I understand.

394
00:33:55,610 --> 00:33:58,370
In that case… I’ll excuse myself.

395
00:33:58,370 --> 00:33:59,600
So you can rest.

396
00:34:19,159 --> 00:34:23,370
Actually… Khun Ngern is the one who wants to apologize to you the most, Khun Po.

397
00:34:25,520 --> 00:34:29,280
But Khun Ngern is very drunk, so Pin asked me to come instead.

398
00:34:30,280 --> 00:34:32,230
Tomorrow Khun Ngern will come talk to you himself, Khun Po.

399
00:34:32,230 --> 00:34:33,460
What’s going on, Inn?

400
00:34:36,260 --> 00:34:37,710
Actually…

401
00:34:37,710 --> 00:34:39,139
Khun Sasom didn’t know about this at all.

402
00:34:40,000 --> 00:34:42,030
He didn’t know Khun Tonnam would come to the wedding tonight.

403
00:34:43,389 --> 00:34:44,750
This was all Khun Ngern’s plan.

404
00:34:45,199 --> 00:34:48,030
He wanted things between you and Khun Sasom to finally be clear.

405
00:34:49,090 --> 00:34:50,000
Besides,

406
00:34:50,920 --> 00:34:53,650
Khun Tonnam left a wound in Khun Sasom’s heart for a long time.

407
00:34:54,750 --> 00:34:56,270
Even after finding him, he didn’t dare meet him.

408
00:34:58,070 --> 00:34:59,400
Even though he had been searching all along.

409
00:35:03,860 --> 00:35:05,100
So that means

410
00:35:06,860 --> 00:35:07,990
P’Ngern

411
00:35:09,040 --> 00:35:11,150
wanted them to face each other.

412
00:35:16,420 --> 00:35:17,090
Yes.

413
00:35:29,760 --> 00:35:31,270
Honestly, I agree.

414
00:35:32,870 --> 00:35:33,880
Because Khun Po

415
00:35:34,780 --> 00:35:36,120
is what makes Khun Sasom happy.

416
00:35:38,880 --> 00:35:40,710
If my boss can settle things with Khun Tonnam,

417
00:35:41,910 --> 00:35:43,810
you two will surely be happier than this.

418
00:35:46,680 --> 00:35:47,470
Alright.

419
00:35:48,920 --> 00:35:49,740
I understand.

420
00:36:05,470 --> 00:36:05,970
Hey.

421
00:36:06,600 --> 00:36:07,140
It’s Ton.

422
00:36:08,140 --> 00:36:08,970
Why

423
00:36:09,630 --> 00:36:11,180
are you acting like you’ve seen a ghost?

424
00:36:12,080 --> 00:36:12,900
Ton.

425
00:36:13,350 --> 00:36:14,340
That hurts my pride.

426
00:36:23,000 --> 00:36:23,750
So,

427
00:36:25,660 --> 00:36:26,810
aren’t you going to introduce

428
00:36:27,820 --> 00:36:28,750
this person to me?

429
00:36:41,880 --> 00:36:42,690
Ton.

430
00:36:42,690 --> 00:36:43,600
This is…

431
00:36:43,600 --> 00:36:44,330
Po.

432
00:36:45,630 --> 00:36:46,220
Po.

433
00:36:46,220 --> 00:36:47,230
This is…

434
00:36:48,180 --> 00:36:48,700
Ton.

435
00:37:00,840 --> 00:37:02,190
Hey, Po.

436
00:37:06,040 --> 00:37:06,790
So…

437
00:37:10,000 --> 00:37:11,010
Lek and

438
00:37:11,960 --> 00:37:13,020
this person

439
00:37:13,370 --> 00:37:14,430
what are you two to each other?

440
00:37:22,400 --> 00:37:23,830
Well, whatever.

441
00:37:25,140 --> 00:37:26,440
Whether you answer or not

442
00:37:27,040 --> 00:37:27,900
it’s fine.

443
00:37:36,520 --> 00:37:38,020
Why don’t we find somewhere to talk, Lek?

444
00:37:38,970 --> 00:37:39,470
Well…

445
00:37:40,620 --> 00:37:43,050
I have a lot to talk to you about.

446
00:37:51,060 --> 00:37:52,100
You can come with us too.

447
00:37:52,400 --> 00:37:53,060
I’m okay.

448
00:37:55,480 --> 00:37:56,460
It’s alright.

449
00:37:57,360 --> 00:37:58,770
You two can go talk.

450
00:38:14,800 --> 00:38:15,300
Wait.

451
00:38:17,650 --> 00:38:18,360
You can come too.

452
00:38:23,200 --> 00:38:24,010
You should go.

453
00:38:24,810 --> 00:38:25,610
I can wait.

454
00:38:34,040 --> 00:38:35,290
Whatever happens, happens.

455
00:38:37,090 --> 00:38:38,490
I’ve been alone my whole life.

456
00:38:40,350 --> 00:38:41,910
Why can’t I be alone again?

457
00:39:31,320 --> 00:39:31,830
Po.

458
00:40:41,840 --> 00:40:43,170
How are you?

459
00:40:47,840 --> 00:40:48,570
I’m fine.

460
00:40:55,760 --> 00:40:56,700
Ton has left.

461
00:41:00,640 --> 00:41:01,880
What do you mean?

462
00:41:06,120 --> 00:41:07,250
It means

463
00:41:09,510 --> 00:41:10,980
he won’t bother you anymore

464
00:41:12,430 --> 00:41:13,390
or me either.

465
00:41:25,020 --> 00:41:25,740
Actually,

466
00:41:29,520 --> 00:41:31,650
I didn’t want to see him from the beginning.

467
00:41:35,440 --> 00:41:37,310
I only tried to contact him

468
00:41:40,480 --> 00:41:42,550
because I wanted to apologize.

469
00:41:44,810 --> 00:41:45,770
I hoped

470
00:41:46,870 --> 00:41:48,830
one day he would forgive me.

471
00:41:52,600 --> 00:41:53,290
And

472
00:41:57,160 --> 00:41:58,510
has he forgiven you yet?

473
00:42:08,000 --> 00:42:08,650
Po.

474
00:42:11,640 --> 00:42:12,490
Well…

475
00:42:20,560 --> 00:42:22,400
I don’t want to film the clip with you anymore.

476
00:42:33,240 --> 00:42:34,580
May I ask why?

477
00:42:44,720 --> 00:42:46,550
Because I like you too much.

478
00:43:27,120 --> 00:43:28,010
Po…

479
00:43:38,640 --> 00:43:40,390
may I ask you something?

480
00:44:08,840 --> 00:44:09,540
I think

481
00:44:14,000 --> 00:44:15,690
we should keep some distance for a while.

482
00:44:30,080 --> 00:44:32,310
I’m not rejecting your feelings.

483
00:44:38,240 --> 00:44:39,740
I just want the two of us

484
00:44:41,740 --> 00:44:42,440
to be sure

485
00:44:44,240 --> 00:44:46,070
that we really want to go on together.

486
00:44:56,280 --> 00:44:57,560
I don’t want to be like my mother,

487
00:45:01,480 --> 00:45:03,090
who chose the wrong man,

488
00:45:07,920 --> 00:45:09,390
and it led to her death.

489
00:45:15,120 --> 00:45:16,440
I couldn’t choose anything.

490
00:45:19,760 --> 00:45:21,350
It became a wound in my heart.

491
00:45:29,000 --> 00:45:30,000
I’m afraid.

492
00:45:32,100 --> 00:45:33,970
I’m afraid I might never be able to love anyone.

493
00:45:44,640 --> 00:45:46,280
But I do feel good about you.

494
00:45:51,520 --> 00:45:53,190
It feels good having you in my life.

495
00:45:56,160 --> 00:45:57,840
It feels good having you around.

496
00:46:03,440 --> 00:46:04,840
I’m very happy.

497
00:46:10,440 --> 00:46:11,600
So happy that

498
00:46:13,250 --> 00:46:15,240
I don’t want to make a mistake.

499
00:46:39,600 --> 00:46:40,840
I understand.

500
00:46:46,680 --> 00:46:47,660
It’s alright.

501
00:46:51,320 --> 00:46:53,130
I’m just as crazy as you.

502
00:47:03,360 --> 00:47:04,420
Tell me then,

503
00:47:07,080 --> 00:47:08,190
what do you want?

504
00:47:20,080 --> 00:47:22,120
I want some distance from you for a while.

505
00:47:29,320 --> 00:47:31,640
I want to be sure

506
00:47:33,540 --> 00:47:35,340
that the person I want to go on with

507
00:47:37,890 --> 00:47:38,930
is Sasom,

508
00:47:40,990 --> 00:47:42,290
not Peach Lover.

509
00:47:45,340 --> 00:47:46,810
Give me one month.

510
00:47:52,040 --> 00:47:52,950
I’m afraid.

511
00:47:55,840 --> 00:47:57,670
I’m afraid I might hurt you.

512
00:48:00,000 --> 00:48:01,490
Give me one month.

513
00:48:05,680 --> 00:48:07,530
If we truly want to go on together,

514
00:48:09,740 --> 00:48:10,870
by that time

515
00:48:15,160 --> 00:48:16,690
I won’t leave you again.

516
00:48:18,290 --> 00:48:19,220
I promise.

517
00:48:26,480 --> 00:48:27,200
Alright.

518
00:49:33,520 --> 00:49:34,370
Wait.

519
00:49:49,800 --> 00:49:50,520
No matter what,

520
00:49:53,880 --> 00:49:55,270
don’t disappear.

521
00:50:00,480 --> 00:50:01,690
I promise

522
00:50:03,190 --> 00:50:04,830
I won’t disappear.

523
00:52:53,480 --> 00:52:54,870
Today I finally understand

524
00:52:57,620 --> 00:52:59,210
that love isn’t easy.

525
00:53:03,120 --> 00:53:04,420
It’s not just smiles

526
00:53:05,230 --> 00:53:06,870
or hugs that warm the heart.

527
00:53:10,640 --> 00:53:12,530
It’s filled with secrets,

528
00:53:14,840 --> 00:53:15,960
fear,

529
00:53:17,370 --> 00:53:18,450
and the past

530
00:53:19,750 --> 00:53:21,280
that you can never escape.

531
00:53:30,400 --> 00:53:31,480
Sasom…

532
00:53:32,180 --> 00:53:34,200
He may see me as his answer.

533
00:53:36,960 --> 00:53:39,000
But I still can’t say with certainty

534
00:53:40,950 --> 00:53:43,230
that he’s truly my final answer.

535
00:53:47,160 --> 00:53:48,650
Because if I choose wrong,

536
00:53:50,600 --> 00:53:51,920
I might lose everything,

537
00:53:54,620 --> 00:53:56,190
just like my mother did.

538
00:54:04,760 --> 00:54:06,710
So I asked him for one month

539
00:54:09,480 --> 00:54:11,040
to make sure

540
00:54:14,320 --> 00:54:16,290
that I truly want to go on with him.

541
00:54:20,400 --> 00:54:22,140
I don’t know what will happen next.

542
00:54:24,840 --> 00:54:25,770
But one thing I know

543
00:54:30,360 --> 00:54:33,090
is that he will never disappear from my memory.

544
00:54:35,040 --> 00:54:36,500
So let’s wait and see

545
00:54:37,800 --> 00:54:38,810
what next month

546
00:54:41,440 --> 00:54:42,930
will bring.

547
00:55:24,080 --> 00:55:25,100
All this time,

548
00:55:25,900 --> 00:55:28,320
maybe I never told you seriously.

549
00:55:29,270 --> 00:55:30,870
I truly love you.

550
00:55:31,470 --> 00:55:33,220
You love me too, don’t you?

551
00:55:34,170 --> 00:55:35,650
I want to see you.

552
00:55:36,810 --> 00:55:38,150
Can you come see me?

553
00:55:44,260 --> 00:55:45,710
Ordain for me, Po.
